body:
**This PR addresses issue #11805**

Major changes:
- The control flow is noticeably changed. Individual becnhmarks can't be prepared/run one by one, so the process now consists of the following steps:
   - build React bundles for local and remote repos;
   - define the list of benchmarks to be run (for local and remote);
   - build all benchmarks, copy them to the server root folder;
   - prepare the runner queue (interleaved or random);
   - start HTTP server and run individual benchmarks according to the queue;
   - gather stats, calculate averages;
   - print results;
- Both local and remote benchmarks now served with the same server instance simultaneously. It allows running benchmarks in any order;
- All benchmarks are served from the `/scripts/bench/public` folder, where they are copied on the preparation step;
- Support for mismatching list of becnhmarks on local and remote branch (i.e. a new benchmark is created locally and not exists on the remote master);
- Support for running benchmarks in the interleaved (default) or random (pass `--order=random`) order;
- **Fix:** the original script seems to be serving only from the local branch becnhmark folder, regardless whether it's local or remote becnhmark run;
